reviews.name: Ulysses
reviews.text:
Visited ProCare Dental in Bangsar, hoping they could tackle my gum concerns, specifically looking into Scaling and Root Planning. Initial chats on WhatsApp were promising – they laid out the expected costs clearly: RM 50 for a consultation, with Scaling and Polishing estimated between RM 200 - RM 300, and potential additional charges depending on treatment specifics.

Dr. Jolene was assigned to my case, stepping in where a periodontist might typically lead. The clinic presented a warm, family-like atmosphere, contrasting with the more sterile environments of cosmetic-focused practices. It was small, yet inviting.

However, as we moved forward, the warm atmosphere was somewhat chilled by Dr. Tan's distant demeanor. Despite this, Dr. Jolene and I discussed my dental plan without settling on the final cost until I was nearly out the door. That’s when I was informed the total could reach RM 350 - RM 500 for Scaling and Polishing, a noticeable jump from our initial conversation.

Seeking clarity, I reached out via WhatsApp, only to be met with silence until the day of my appointment. Their response sidestepped my pricing concerns, asking if I planned to attend without addressing my questions. Disappointed by this lapse in communication, I decided to cancel my visit, informing them that their silence had been a deciding factor.

In sum, while ProCare Dental initially seemed a promising choice, with clear upfront costs and a friendly, homely vibe, the experience took a turn due to poor communication and an unexpected increase in quoted prices. Despite the potential for a positive dental experience, my search for the right dental care continues, guided by both the need for transparency and a more responsive approach

reviews.text:
I went here for my baby because I wanted to do sapuan florida for her. I just walked in since babies and senior citizens have a fast lane.

After my baby settled, I went ahead and registered myself as a walk in patient. The nurse said actually they can accept walk ins depending on how busy it is and you need to come very early because by 7.45am people are already lining up downstairs and the guard will give out the numbers.

While waiting, my baby fell asleep. She had a fever and couldn’t sleep well last night, so I really didn’t want to disturb her. I called my husband to come.

While waiting, my number got called and I told the nurse I was waiting for my husband to hold the baby and they could call someone else first. I felt terribly sorry, but they were all very kind and understanding.

As a mom who came with a baby, you know how much this means and touches your heart.

And let me tell you guys about the service, it’s sooooo good! My teeth have never felt this clean after a scaling session. The nurses and doctors were all so kind and treated my baby so well.

Truly one of the best experiences I’ve had at a government clinic! Professional, gentle, and full of warmth. Thank you to all the staff for being so patient and caring. Highly recommended!

reviews.name: Annie Wong
reviews.text:
Dr Suresh has been taking care of our family for over a decade now. He's just amazing which is why even though we have migrated to Australia, we still make it a point to visit him every time we head to Malaysia. He always recommends a course of action that takes into consideration the financial side of things, whether it's convenient for us, whether it is absolutely necessary and whether the solution makes sense for us over the longer term. He weighs it all out for us. Very transparent. No pressure ever and no unnecessary upselling. He even offered to speak to our Australia dentist if we preferred to have it done in our new home. And the best part, he really cares about his patients. My mother had dentures made by Dr Suresh and she had leave for Singapore to live with my brother. She didn't manage to make her final appointment with Dr Suresh to do final tweaks for her dentures. Concerned, Dr Suresh contacted his dentist friend in Singapore to ask him to take good care of my mum and help her. He really went out of his way. And my husband had an implant before we moved to Australia and when we visited next, Dr Suresh wasn't too pleased with how it was healing and he gave my husband additional treatments to make sure the implant was completed perfectly and comfortably for my husband. And what I really like is also the fact that he invests what he makes back into his business. You can see that he takes a lot of pride in what he does because his practice always adopts the latest technology. During our visit last month, he was using a teeth scanner which I have only seen in one of the dental clinics I brought my son to here in Australia and I remember asking the dentist about it and being told it was a very expensive high-end piece of technology/equipment. It's a long review but having been his patients for over a decade, we can't help but have so many wonderful experiences to share. We trust him completely and we are grateful that he continues to be our family dentist (myself, my husband, our son and my mother).

PS: His frontdesk is super efficient, helpful and friendly too! And regardless of the clinic's success, they remain humble and always eager to help.
reviews.responseFromOwnerText:
Annie, thank you for taking the time to share this. Reading about your family’s experiences over the years - and knowing you still make the journey from Australia to see us - is deeply meaningful.
What you’ve described about Dr. Suresh’s approach is exactly what we strive for: care that considers the whole picture, not just the immediate treatment. What you shared reflects the kind of relationships we hope to build with every patient.
It’s particularly touching that you’ve noticed how we invest back into the practice. Staying current with technology matters to us because it helps us provide better care, but it’s the trust families like yours place in us that truly drives everything we do.
We’re honored to continue caring for you, your husband, your son, and your mother across the miles. Thank you for letting us be part of your family’s story for more than a decade.
Our front desk team will be so pleased to read your kind words about them as well.
With gratitude,
Pristine Dental Centre

My boyfriend and I found WeSmile through google reviews. I contacted their office on whatsapp, they were very responsive and helpful in scheduling a consultation for a cleaning and wisdom tooth extraction for me and a crown for my boyfriend.

We met with Dr. Scully and it was the friendliest dentist visit we've ever had. My teeth cleaning and extraction was quick and painless. My boyfriend had a "peg" lateral incisor that he wanted to get something unique done to it. We had contacted a few other clinics and they were not used to doing gold crowns, mainly zirconia (natural color). Dr Scully and his team were very accommodating with kind of an unusual request.

The crown took 2 visits to complete. The first day took about 2 hours in the chair- consult, making sure that was what he wanted, double checking that was what he wanted, an x-ray was taken to ensure that the tooth was healthy as well as to understand the underlying root structure of the tooth before minimally shaving down the sides in order to provide more clearance for the crown. Great care was taken to ensure good fitment and no interference with the bite. A temporary cap was set as a placeholder as we waited for the lab to make the gold cap(expedited to 6 days). There were two options, 50% and 78% gold content. Dr. Scully explained each step of the process thoroughly to us and we gained an appreciation for the art of esthetic dentistry.

The second visit was very quick, only about an hour. Essentially consisted of popping off the temporary crown, prepping and bonding the gold cap and final adjustments making sure that fitment was perfect with the bite. I'll let the pictures speak for themselves. my boyfriend is very happy with the result. Don't hesitate to visit WeSmile dental clinic for any and all needs. The cherry on top was the great food recommendations sent by Dr. Scully and his team, the perfect pairing for a new smile and healthy teeth.

reviews.name: Jenz Fotos
reviews.text:
The promotion price and communication over WhatsApp are good.  I needed three fillings.  The dentist told me that I didn't need to be numbed which was true for two of my teeth.  The third tooth was extremely painful after the existing filling was removed. I kept pulling away, vocalizing my pain and sobbing in the chair.

I was made to feel that my pain was an inconvenience, being told to hold still, that I am being too sensitive, that I don't have a tolerance for pain and just little bit more.  There was a lack of empathy.

That kind of pain is not possible to hold still for.  I am not weak.  I suffer through kidney stones without tears.  I left here feeling physically and emotionally wrecked.

When she finished, I was biting only on the filling.  The rest of my teeth weren't able to touch each other.  She raised my chair as if she was finished and told me it would work itself out in a few days.  I had to insist to get the bite fixed because it was wildly uncomfortable.  She did that with impatience and I left still biting primarily on that tooth.

Overnight a piece broke off and my bite normalized.  I went back the next day (with great hesitation) and she resealed it.  More pain and tears shed during this work, and somehow this was my fault.  At least I was not charged for the rework.

I can't recommend this place for people who struggle to advocate for themselves or for people who can afford to to elsewhere.

Edit to provide response to the Dental office's reply (screenshot attached in photos):

-> All treatments were performed in accordance with standard clinical protocols, including assessing the need for local anesthesia

[Perhaps you need to revisit your protocols as the pain during my visit was unbearable.  No one should experience this ever.]

-> Pain perception varies between individuals, and ... some sensitivity is expected.

[You continue to minimize the pain that I experienced just like you did during the procedure.  By referring to it as "some sensitivity," you continue to disregard the level of pain that I have reported to you.]

-> especially when working on previously restored or worn teeth.

[Should patients come with only pristine teeth?  Are you not capable of managing pain for patients with worn out teeth?]

-> When you returned the following day, we provided a reassessment at no additional charge.

[The new filling broke overnight, I would hope you wouldn't charge to repair it.]

-> Our dentist also recommended taking a 3D X-ray to rule out any other causes of pain, but you declined because...

[I declined because I had no intention of undergoing more procedures with you.  I wanted the broken filling repaired and only that.]

-> During both visits, the dentist asked again if you required local anesthesia.

[You did not.  It is indeed the first thing I asked you about when you started drilling without as I was quite surprised and you told me it wouldn't be unnecessary.  Indeed it wasn't necessary for the other two teeth.]

-> but there was no clear communication from your end.

[I communicated that I was in pain, you just disregarded it.  You asked "is it pain or sensitivity' repeatedly I told you it was pain and to be more clear I said "you are hurting me," and you just completely disregarded that and replied, but is it just sensitivity?  If my words weren't clear to you, my sobbing, yelping and hyperventilating should have been clues.  You seemed more inconvenienced by my pain than concerned and kept pushing me to continue.]

-> We remain committed to providing safe, ethical, and patient-focused care.

[Then listen and learn from what I am telling you.  That was the most traumatizing dental/medical visit of my life and you should put anyone else through thia experience again again.]

You never had a word of empathy.  You didn't listen, just 100% defensive and trying to make it my fault for being "too sensitive" and having a "worn tooth."
reviews.responseFromOwnerText:
Thank you for taking the time to share your feedback. We are sorry to hear that your experience did not meet your expectations. However, we would like to clarify several important points regarding your visit.

All treatments were performed in accordance with standard clinical protocols, including assessing the need for local anesthesia and ensuring your bite was checked and adjusted when requested. Our dentist also informed you that your lower left tooth was already significantly worn down, exposing the dentin layer, which naturally causes increased sensitivity. Before beginning the procedure, a topical numbing gel was applied, and throughout the treatment the dentist repeatedly checked on you and asked if you were alright.

Pain perception varies between individuals, and while we always strive to keep patients comfortable, some sensitivity is expected—especially when working on previously restored or worn teeth. Our team took care to explain each step and respond to your reactions during the procedure.

When you returned the following day, we provided a reassessment at no additional charge. Our dentist also recommended taking a 3D X-ray to rule out any other causes of pain, but you declined because you did not have enough time. During both visits, the dentist asked again if you required local anesthesia, but there was no clear communication from your end.

We remain committed to providing safe, ethical, and patient-focused care. We would be happy to review you again to address any remaining discomfort or clarify any misunderstandings.

reviews.textTranslated:
My silver filling suddenly fell out, so I quickly went to a nearby dentist I found.
The appointment went smoothly, as the WhatsApp message was read immediately.
I hadn't had a cleaning since coming to Malaysia, so I also had a whitening treatment, which I'd been interested in for a while.

When I went to the Japanese-run Hibari Dental Clinic before, they were thorough, taking X-rays beforehand (as is common in Japan), but it was still quite expensive. Unlike in Japan, insurance doesn't cover it in Malaysia. 🥲

However, this clinic quickly addressed my issue (a loose filling).
They also didn't push me to get anything unnecessarily expensive for the cleaning and whitening, so it was much cheaper than I expected. In fact, while a similar procedure would normally require three visits in Japan, it was all done in less than 1.5 hours per session.

The dentist and staff were very kind.
I'll definitely choose this dentist again if I have any problems.
Thank you so much!
